  "response": "Yes, pigs can show affection. They are intelligent, social animals that form strong bonds with humans and other pigs. Some ways pigs show affection include:\n\n1. Nuzzling or leaning against their human caretakers\n2. Wagging their tails\n3. Making soft grunting or purring sounds\n4. Seeking physical contact and wanting to be petted\n5. Following their owners around\n6. Playing and showing excitement when seeing familiar people\n\nPigs are known to be quite emotionally complex and can develop deep, meaningful relationships with humans and other animals.",
